{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-21T15:08:05.906Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Two Pointers"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Sliding Window"},{"type":"text","text":" are array/string optimization patterns that replace nested loops with single-pass traversal, reducing time complexity from O(n²) to O(n). "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Two Pointers"},{"type":"text","text":" use two indices to converge from ends or track positions independently (sorted arrays, pairs, palindromes), while "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Sliding Window"},{"type":"text","text":" maintains a bounded segment between two pointers (fixed or variable size) for substring/subarray problems. In Gen AI, these patterns enable efficient "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"token sequence processing"},{"type":"text","text":" (sliding window attention), "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"duplicate detection"},{"type":"text","text":" (two pointers for sorted token IDs), and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"window-based feature extraction"},{"type":"text","text":" (NLP context windows)."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Two Pointers Technique"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What It Is"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Aspect"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Definition"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"t